(42, 1, 80, 42, 2, 52, 52, 'grew, and waxed strong in spirit', 'Growth of Key Figures', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth in both passages. John the Baptist is described as growing strong in spirit, while Jesus is noted for increasing in wisdom and stature.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 80, 9, 3, 19, 20, 'grew, and waxed strong in spirit', 'Growth and Prophetic Establishment', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth in both passages, as both John and Samuel are described as having grown strong and established in their roles. The mention of their growth and divine presence emphasizes their significance as prophets in Israel.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 80, 40, 3, 1, 1, 'in the deserts', 'John the Baptist''s Wilderness Ministry', 'This connection highlights John''s growth and preparation in the wilderness before his public ministry. Both passages emphasize his presence in the deserts and wilderness, indicating a significant phase in his life leading to his role as a preacher.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 80, 7, 13, 24, 25, 'the child grew', 'Connection of Growth and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of a child and the movement of the Spirit of the Lord. In Luke, the child grows strong in spirit, while in Judges, the Spirit of the Lord begins to move Samson.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
