(42, 2, 1, 42, 3, 1, 1, 'Cesar Augustus', 'Connection of Roman Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Roman leaders in governing Judea. The decree from Caesar Augustus in Luke 2:1 sets the stage for the political context in which Tiberius Caesar reigns in Luke 3:1.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 1, 40, 24, 14, 14, 'all the world', 'Connection of Global Reach', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''all the world'' in both passages. Luke 2:1 refers to a decree affecting the entire world, while Matthew 24:14 speaks of the gospel being preached in all the world.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
