(42, 2, 1, 44, 11, 28, 28, 'all the world', 'Connection of Decrees and Dearth', 'This connection highlights the influence of Roman authority in both passages. The decree from Caesar Augustus in Luke sets the stage for the socio-political context, while the prophecy of a great dearth during Claudius Caesar''s reign indicates the ongoing impact of such decrees on the world.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 1, 45, 1, 8, 8, 'all the world', 'Connection of Global Impact', 'This connection highlights the theme of global significance. The decree from Caesar Augustus affects ''all the world,'' while the faith mentioned in Romans is ''spoken of throughout the whole world.''', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
