(42, 2, 2, 40, 4, 24, 24, 'Syria', 'Connection through Syria', 'This connection highlights the geographical reference to Syria in both passages. Luke mentions Cyrenius as governor of Syria during the census, while Matthew notes Jesus'' fame spreading throughout Syria as he healed many. Both passages emphasize the significance of Syria in the context of Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 2, 44, 13, 7, 7, 'governor of Syria', 'Governance and Authority in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of governance, as both passages mention figures in positions of authority: Cyrenius as governor and Sergius Paulus as deputy. Both contexts involve significant events in the early Christian narrative.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 2, 44, 18, 12, 12, 'governor of Syria', 'Governance and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of governing authorities during significant events. In Luke, Cyrenius is mentioned as governor, while in Acts, Gallio is identified as the deputy, highlighting the political context surrounding the events.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 2, 44, 23, 26, 26, 'governor of Syria', 'Governance in Biblical Context', 'This connection highlights the role of governance in both passages. Luke mentions Cyrenius as governor, while Acts refers to Felix as governor, emphasizing the significance of political authority in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 2, 44, 26, 30, 30, 'governor', 'Governance and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a governor in significant events. In Luke, Cyrenius is mentioned as governor during a census, while in Acts, a governor is present during a royal assembly.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 4, 33, 5, 2, 2, 'the city of David, which is called Bethlehem', 'Connection of Birthplace Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the significance of Bethlehem as the birthplace of a ruler in Israel. Luke 2:4 identifies Bethlehem as the city where Joseph went, fulfilling the prophecy in Micah 5:2 about a ruler coming from Bethlehem.', 'prophecy', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 4, 43, 7, 42, 42, 'the city of David, which is called Bethlehem', 'Connection of David and Bethlehem', 'This connection highlights the significance of Bethlehem as the birthplace of Christ, linking both passages through the mention of ''the seed of David'' and ''the town of Bethlehem.'' Both verses affirm Jesus'' Davidic lineage and his connection to Bethlehem.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 4, 9, 16, 1, 1, 'city of David, which is called Bethlehem', 'Connection of David''s Lineage', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Bethlehem as the city linked to David. Luke highlights Joseph''s lineage to David, while 1 Samuel introduces Jesse, a Bethlehemite, as the father of David, establishing a direct connection between the two texts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 4, 8, 4, 17, 17, 'house and lineage of David', 'Lineage of David Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the lineage of David. Luke 2:4 mentions Joseph''s descent from David, while Ruth 4:17 highlights Obed as the grandfather of David.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 4, 40, 2, 23, 23, 'city of David, which is called Bethlehem', 'Connection of Locations and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the movement from Bethlehem to Nazareth, emphasizing Jesus'' origins and fulfillment of prophecy. Both passages emphasize the significance of these locations in relation to Jesus'' identity.', 'prophecy', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
